      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "MarkdownNote"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Chest / upper torso masked inpaint\n\nGoal:\n\noriginal image -> manual chest/upper torso mask -> inpaint only that area -> use original image as visual reference -> low/medium denoise -> compare outfit consistency.\n\nMask rules:\n\n- Use a separate black/white mask image.\n- White = editable chest / upper torso / shirt region.\n- Black = protected.\n- Keep face, hair, and neck black if possible.\n- Include enough surrounding shirt/torso context so fabric tension can change naturally.\n- For silhouette changes, include a small band around the body edge.\n\nPrompt intent:\n\nPreserve same face, hair, pose, lighting, camera, and outfit design. Only adjust chest/upper torso shape under the same shirt.\n\nStart conservative. Default denoise is 0.40 through SplitSigmasDenoise. If the outfit changes, lower denoise/CFG, reduce the mask area, or make the prompt more explicit."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653",
      "title": "MarkdownNote"
    },
